from datetime import datetime

def comp_str_to_int(s: str) -> int:
    if s == "N/A":
        return 0
    assert "K" in s
    s = s.split("K", 1)[0]
    return int(float(s) * 1000)

def load_csv(fname: str) -> pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(fname, sep="\t")
    return pd.DataFrame({
        "location": [lad.split(" | ", 1)[0] for lad in df.locationAndDate],
        "datetime": [datetime.strptime(lad.split(" | ", 1)[1], "%m/%d/%Y") for lad in df.locationAndDate],
        "level": [int(level_str.split("L")[1]) for level_str in df.level],
        "role": [topic for topic in df.topic],
        "experience": [int(yoe.split(" yrs", 1)[0].split(" yr", 1)[0]) for yoe in df.yoe],
        "comp": [int(comp.split("$", 1)[1].replace(",", "")) for comp in df.totalComp],
        "base": [comp_str_to_int(comp.split(" | ")[0]) for comp in df.compSplit],
        "stock": [comp_str_to_int(comp.split(" | ")[1]) for comp in df.compSplit],
        "bonus": [comp_str_to_int(comp.split(" | ")[2]) for comp in df.compSplit],
    })

df = load_csv("data.tsv")

tmp = df[df.level == 4].sort_values("comp")
x = [f"{i + 1}/{len(tmp)}" for i in range(len(tmp))]
y = tmp.comp / 1000
plt.figure(dpi=300)
plt.scatter(x, y)
plt.plot(x, y)
plt.xlabel(f"{len(tmp)} Recent L4 Eng Hires")
plt.ylabel("Total Comp (thousands of $)")
plt.show()
